a slow or irregular heartbeat.', 'Synergism', 'Caution is advised if angiotensin II receptor blockers must be used concurrently with potassium-sparing diuretics, particularly in patients with renal impairment, diabetes, old age, severe or worsening heart failure, dehydration, or concomitant therapy with other agents that increase serum potassium such as nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs, beta-blockers, cyclosporine, heparin, tacrolimus, and trimethoprim.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/59253/', '', 'Sacubitril', '', 1767369485);
